	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=68250><span id=Sage>OnetreeTallbarque</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>23 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The Coldain in Thurgadin do indeed keel over dead but ONLY if the war in the Great Divide is lost. This effect lasts for some minutes and then the zone repops back to normal. I've seen it just once and that's enough.<br><br>The giants drop "glowing velium" weapons with lousy stats. They're junk. Sometimes I pick one up if I get a breather (I'm usually a kiter) for selling to a merchant. It's good for some small change.<br><br>The giants are not Frost Giants per se, they are Kromrif Recruits, Kromrif Warriors, Kromrif Captains, Priests of Zek, etc. on up to Narandi the Wretched himself. Frost Giants are easy to solo. These Kromrif/Kromzek, on the other hand, are worthy of your best might, magic and tactics on a large scale. An hour's preparation and three hours or so of war can mean up to SIX uber upgrades for participants.<br><br>Yes, the loot is great. But perhaps most satisfying of all is the knowledge that you and all your friends have succeeded at an unusual, massive, and incredibly fun challenge. And THAT is worth all the trials and tribulations of one's early EQ life. Best of luck!</p>&nbsp;<br>Onetree Tallbarque &lt;Valoran&gt;<br>Hierophant & PoM Pilot, Karana Server<br>Magelo Advisor & Keeper of the PoM FAQ<br>Grandmaster Jeweler<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21159" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21159</a></td></td></tr>
